<%# Single canonical heat bar (the two-variant pick-off was collapsed
    once the user re-locked on the three-zone solid-ends pattern).
    The numeric label is intentionally absent — the gradient +
    indicator tick encode the score on their own. See
    `rating_heat_bar_component.rb` for the score-synthesis logic and
    the three-zone (solid 0-25 / solid 25-50 / gradient 50-90 /
    solid 90-100) layout.

    Wave C reveal — when `game.resyncing?` is true we render the FULL
    bar (not the muted variant) with `--score: 0` and the bubble text
    forced to em-dash. The indicator tick + bubble both park at the
    left edge; on Turbo morph after sync complete the rendered DOM
    carries the real `--score`, and the CSS `transition: left 600ms
    ease-in-out` rule animates the tick + bubble rightward to their
    final position. %>
<% s = score %>
<% if resyncing? %>
  <div class="rating-heat-bar"
       data-resyncing="yes"
       data-tier="missing"
       style="--score: <%= score_var %>; --tier-color: var(--color-muted);">
    <span class="rating-heat-bar-bubble"><%= bubble_text %></span>
    <div class="rating-heat-bar-indicator"></div>
  </div>
<% elsif s %>
  <div class="rating-heat-bar"
       data-score="<%= s %>"
       data-tier="<%= tier %>"
       style="--score: <%= s %>; --tier-color: var(--color-rating-<%= tier %>);">
    <span class="rating-heat-bar-bubble"><%= s %></span>
    <div class="rating-heat-bar-indicator"></div>
  </div>
<% else %>
  <div class="rating-heat-bar rating-heat-bar--muted"
       data-tier="missing"></div>
<% end %>
